HEADWORD: Altarwise
<hw>Al"tar*wise`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In the proper
position of an altar, that is, at the east of a church with its ends
towards the north and south.</def> <rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

